    "content" : "You need the spacer (spigot ring) for the CSP brakes, but if you don't want the backing plates just knock them off, which will act as a drift, otherwise you need a bearing puller that clamps around the spigot ring and has like a razor edge that is forced under the spacer as it's tightend up. It can then be pulled off.",
